  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Add beef kidney and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Remove kidney and set aside.",
    "Add more oil if necessary, then saut\u00155 ginger and garlic until fragrant.",
    "Add soy sauce, yuzu juice, and black pepper, stirring to combine.",
    "Return the beef kidney to the pot and stir to coat with the sauce.",
    "Add the chopped scallions and bok choy, and stir-fry for 2-3 minutes.",
    "Add enough water to the pot to cover the ingredients and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer, covered, until the kidney is tender, about 20 minutes.",
    "Season with salt to taste and serve hot."
